      <chapter eId="chp_319i">
        <num>319i</num>
        <heading>Connecticut HUSKY Plan</heading>
        <section eId="sec_17a_460d">
          <num>17a-460d</num>
          <heading>Connecticut Mental Health Center: Other contracts</heading>
          <subsection eId="17a_460d__subsec_a">
            <num>(a)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Whenever the commissioner deems it appropriate and grants approval, the center may enter into contracts, agreements, leases, or other arrangements for the following:</p>
            </content>
            <paragraph eId="17a_460d__subsec_a__subsec_1">
              <num>(1)</num>
              <content>
                <p>The acquisition of commodities, goods, services and equipment;</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph eId="17a_460d__subsec_a__subsec_2">
              <num>(2)</num>
              <content>
                <p>office, clinic, laboratory or other needed space whether on or off the center's main campus; and</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph eId="17a_460d__subsec_a__subsec_3">
              <num>(3)</num>
              <content>
                <p>necessary capital expenditures.</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="17a_460d__subsec_b">
            <num>(b)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Contracts, agreements, leases or other arrangements approved under this section by the commissioner shall not be subject to the review or approval of other state agencies or any other state-mandated purchasing or acquisition procedures, unless and to the extent the commissioner deems it necessary.
(Return to ChapterTable of Contents)(Return toList of Chapters)(Return toList of Titles)</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
        </section>
      </chapter>
